  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) operating conditions. The computational model is intended to predict absolute hemolysis index levels for a Class III implantable VAD at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 credibility factors; seven factors were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps. All assessed factors achieved levels at or above their required gradations under the Minimal profile review. Intended-use scope, patient population, and operating envelope are described in the bound Requirement and Claim nodes; the structured Context of Use object is not separately linked per ProfileMinimal conventions. Decision: Accepted.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-requirement",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-prediction-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench-dataset"
  ],
